content:
Enforce View Roles and Role Hierarchy Permission When Editing Public List View Visibility (Release Update)

With this update, only users with the View Roles and Role Hierarchy permission can see or select from your organization’s list of roles when they edit public list view visibility. This was first available in Spring ’24 and scheduled for enforcement in Winter ’25, but postponed to Spring ’25.

Where: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer editions in Lightning Experience and Salesforce Classic.

When: Enforced in Spring ’25. Get the major release upgrade date for your instance by going to Trust Status.

Why: This security update blocks users with only the Manage Public List Views permission from seeing roles and role hierarchies when editing public list views.

How: To edit public list views, a user needs the Manage Public List Views permission. Grant them the View Roles and Role Hierarchy permission as well for access to roles. Alternatively, have a user with the View Roles and Role Hierarchy permission grant access to list views.

To view this update, enter Release Updates in Setup’s Quick Find box and select Release Updates. Follow the testing and activation steps for Enforce View Roles and Role Hierarchy Permission When Editing Public List View Visibility.
title: Enforcing Role Hierarchy Permission for Public List Views
